  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How I recover my Facebook password?",
  "response": "If you've forgotten your Facebook password, you can recover it by following these steps:\n\n### 1. **Go to the Facebook Login Page**\n   - Open your web browser and navigate to [Facebook's login page](https://www.facebook.com).\n\n### 2. **Click on \"Forgot Password?\"**\n   - Below the login fields, click on the link that says **\"Forgot Password?\"**.\n\n### 3. **Enter Your Email, Phone Number, or Username**\n   - You'll be prompted to enter the email address, phone number, or username associated with your Facebook account.\n\n### 4. **Choose a Recovery Method**\n   - Facebook will provide options to recover your account, such as:\n     - **Email**: A password reset link will be sent to your registered email.\n     - **Text Message (SMS)**: A code will be sent to your phone.\n     - **Google Account**: If you\u2019ve linked your Google account, you can use it to reset your password.\n\n### 5. **Follow the Instructions**\n   - Depending on the method you choose, follow the instructions provided:\n     - If you receive an email, open it and click the password reset link.\n     - If you receive a text message, enter the code on Facebook\u2019s recovery page.\n\n### 6. **Create a New Password**\n   - Once you verify your identity, you\u2019ll be prompted to create a new password. Make sure it\u2019s strong and unique.\n\n### 7. **Log In with Your New Password**\n   - After resetting your password, use it to log in to your Facebook account.\n\n### **Troubleshooting Tips**\n   - **Don\u2019t have access to your email or phone?** Click **\"No longer have access to these?\"** during the recovery process and follow the steps to verify your identity using other methods.\n   - **Account Hacked?** If you suspect your account was hacked, visit [Facebook\u2019s Hacked Account page](https://www.facebook.com/hacked) for help.\n\n### **Prevent Future Issues**\n   - Make sure your email and phone number are up to date in your Facebook account settings.\n   - Enable **two-factor authentication** for added security.\n\nIf you\u2019re still having trouble, you can visit [Facebook's Help Center](https://www.facebook.com/help) for additional support.",
